{"actual_usd":0.15539499999999998,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":140,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30659,"reply":"\"I don't think I could keep calling it Christianity, no.\" *I rub my thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and let the morning light sit a moment on my sleeve.* \"Paul says, 'If Christ be not raised, your faith is vain'—and I believe he meant it plain.\"\n\n*I lift one shoulder, not dramatic, just honest.* \"My faith would change completely. I might still admire parts of Jesus's teaching, same way a man can admire a good doctor he can no longer call living—but the thing itself, the hope that death was beaten in the flesh, the mercy that doesn't end at the grave... that rises or falls with the resurrection.\"","rolling_24h_usd":79.60381499999995,"run_id":"e2094ccd-f93f-45c9-802a-10ea5fece227"}
